com.facebook.buck.rules

Class AbstractCachingBuildRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractCachingBuildRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BuildRule, Comparable<BuildRule>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoNotUseAbstractBuildable

    @Beta
public abstract class AbstractCachingBuildRule
extends Object
implements BuildRule
    Abstract implementation of a BuildRule that can be cached. If its current RuleKey matches the one on disk, then it has no work to do. It should also try to fetch its output from an ArtifactCache to avoid doing any computation.

      • appendToRuleKey

        public RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder)
                                throws IOException
        getRuleKey() and getRuleKeyWithoutDeps() uses this when constructing RuleKeys for this class. Every subclass that extends the rule state in a way that matters to idempotency must override appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) and append its state to the RuleKey.Builder returned by its superclass's appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) implementation. Example: 
         @Override
 protected RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder) {
   return super.appendToRuleKey(builder)
       .set("srcs", srcs),
       .set("resources", resources);
 }
        Throws:
        IOException

      • initializeFromDisk

        protected void initializeFromDisk(OnDiskBuildInfo onDiskBuildInfo)
        For a rule that is read from the build cache, it may have fields that would normally be populated by executing the steps returned by Buildable.getBuildSteps(BuildContext, BuildableContext). Because Buildable.getBuildSteps(BuildContext, BuildableContext) is not invoked for cached rules, a rule may need to implement this method to populate those fields in some other way. For a cached rule, this method will be invoked just before the future returned by build(BuildContext) is resolved.
        Parameters:
        onDiskBuildInfo - can be used to read metadata from disk to help initialize the rule.

      • getDeps

        public final ImmutableSortedSet<BuildRule> getDeps()
        Specified by:
        getDeps in interface BuildRule
        Returns:
        the set of rules that must be built before this rule. Normally, this matches the value of the deps argument for this build rule in the build file in which it was defined.

        However, there are special cases where other arguments pull in implicit dependencies (e.g., the keystore argument in android_binary). In these cases, the implicit dependencies are also included in the set returned by this method. The value of the original deps argument, as defined in the build file, must be accessed via a custom getter provided by the build rule.
